The paper proposes a hierarchical controller for autonomous racing that involves motion planning and optimization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a nonlinear model predictive path following controller, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and trajectory planning, which are topics covered in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of computer vision for racing, which falls under the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
